properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 19 at 3:58PM EST until February 21 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 15 to 20 knots with gusts up to 30 knots and
seas 4 to 6 feet are expected.

* WHERE...The coastal waters from Little Egg Inlet, New Jersey to
Fenwick Island, Delaware.

* WHEN...From midnight Thursday night until 4:00 PM Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT THURSDAY NIGHT TO 4 PM EST FRIDAY
